Q1.Populate ticket_created_at column in feedbacks table using created_at from ticket table

Solution:

Using  VLOOKUP to fetch the created_at value from the ticket sheet

Formula:
=VLOOKUP(A2, ticket!A:E, 2, FALSE)

Explanation:

A2 → cms_id in feedback table
ticket!A:E → ticket worksheet range
2 → column containing created_at
FALSE → exact match

This formula fills the ticket_created_at column
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q2.Fetch outlet-wise count of tickets created and closed

a) Closed on same day

Creating  a new column in ticket sheet

Formula:
=IF(DATE(created_at)=DATE(closed_at),"Same Day","No")

Then using  Pivot Table

Steps:
Select ticket data
Click Insert → Pivot Table
Add outlet_id → Rows
Add ticket_id → Values (Count)
Filter Same Day
-----------------------------
b)Closed in same hour

Creating  another column

Formula:
=IF(HOUR(created_at)=HOUR(closed_at),"Same Hour","No")

Then using  Pivot Table again to count tickets per outlet.
